<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-12-08T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-12-08T10:00:00-05:00" n="446" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d446">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.2531/230: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Frost</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-08T11:00:00-04:00">December 8, 1937—11
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received December 8—10:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>89. Department’s 55, December 2, 4 p.m. Foreign Office here approved
                            interpretation of item (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) contained in my
                            telegram 80;<note n="46" xml:id="d446fn46">November 22, 7 p.m., <ref target="#pg_417">p. 417</ref>.</note> but García at Buenos
                            Aires, to whom it was air mailed, has unexpectedly raised objections to
                            fourth sentence, regarding recourse to <pb facs="0434" n="424" xml:id="pg_424"/> import quotas. A modification of this sentence may
                            be submitted to the Department by telegraph tomorrow. García’s return
                            now set for early next week.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Frost</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>